x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Silicon Valley is o=
n the march in Washington=E2=80=94and nowhere is its arrival more apparent =
than in <b>Donald Trump</b>=E2=80=99s strikingly tech-friendly circle of ad=
visors and hangers-on, who have gotten themselves appointed to key agency r=
oles, become top surrogates for the incoming administration, or secured =E2=
=80=9Cczar=E2=80=9D titles that didn=E2=80=99t previously exist. =E2=80=9CI=
t=E2=80=99s more likely for the administration to take action than Congress=
,=E2=80=9D said <b>Nu Wexler</b>, a tech communications consultant who prev=
iously worked for Twitter, Facebook, and Google. =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t t=
hink there are high expectations for this Congress with a one- to three-vot=
e majority in the House. Also, given the history of Congress not acting on =
tech legislation over the last eight years, it just hasn=E2=80=99t been pos=
sible.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Meanwhile, Trump=E2=80=99s kitchen cabinet is bein=
g stocked with tech
moguls, entrepreneurs, and venture capitalists who have flocked to Mar-a-La=
go to curry favor with the president-elect. <b>Elon Musk</b>=E2=80=94practi=
cally an honorary Trump at this point=E2=80=94is supposedly in charge, alon=
g with <b>Vivek Ramaswamy</b>, of cutting government red tape via the new a=
nd still effectively powerless DOGE committee. <b>Peter Thiel </b>prot=C3=
=A9g=C3=A9 <b>J.D. Vance</b> will soon decamp to the Naval Observatory. And=
 earlier this week, Trump named the tech investor and <i>All-In</i> podcast=
er <b>David Sacks</b>, whose campaign fundraiser at his San Francisco home =
presaged Silicon Valley=E2=80=99s rightward tilt, as his =E2=80=9CA.I. and =
Crypto czar,=E2=80=9D a title in search of a portfolio.<br/><br/>Others app=
ear to be forging less formal alliances, or at least smoothing things over =
with the once-and-future president. <b>Mark Zuckerberg</b> headed down to P=
alm Beach to pay his respects=E2=80=94and pledge $1 million to the Trump In=
auguration, a sum <b>Jeff Bezos</b> and OpenAI=E2=80=99s<b> Sam
Altman</b> each matched a day later. Salesforce C.E.O. <b>Marc Benioff</b>,=
 the owner of <i>Time </i>magazine=E2=80=94which just selected Trump as its=
 2024 Person of the Year=E2=80=94recently heralded the moment as =E2=80=9Ca=
 time of great promise for our nation.=E2=80=9D And while he has no officia=
l role, venture capitalist <b>Marc Andreessen</b> told <b>Bari Weiss </b>th=
at since the election, he=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cspent half his time at Mar-a-L=
ago.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
